25|$|The Knesset {{established}} this observance in 2014. The {{purpose of}} this observance is to recognize the collective trauma of Mizrahi Jews during the period around {{the establishment of the}} State of Israel. Many Mizrachi Jews felt that their own suffering was being ignored, both in comparison <b>to</b> <b>the</b> <b>suffering</b> of European Jewry during the Holocaust and in comparison to the Palestinian Nakba. The Gregorian-calendar date chosen is the day after the United Nations Partition Plan for Palestine was adopted, as that date marked the beginning of concentrated pressure and hostility against the community.|$|E
